'''''Saaku Magalu''''' ({{lang-kn|ಸಾಕು ಮಗಳು, English : Foster Daughter}}) is a 1963 [[Kannada language]] [[romantic drama]] film directed and produced by [[B. R. Panthulu]] and starring [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] and [[Sowcar Janaki]] in the lead roles.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0250710/fullcredits/ Full cast & crew]</ref> The film marked the entry of acclaimed actress [[Kalpana (Kannada actress)|Kalpana]], who went on to become one of the most sought-after actresses in Kannada cinema.

[[B. R. Panthulu]] made the movie simultaneously in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''[[Pempudu Koothuru]]'', starring [[N. T. Rama Rao|NTR]], [[Devika]] and [[Sowcar Janaki]].

